<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="search-v">search <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /sɜːtʃ/    美 /sɜːrtʃ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(在...中) 搜寻</strong></h4>
<p>to look carefully for sth / sb：</p>
<ul>
<li>search (sth) for:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police searched the house for the stolen jewelry.
警察搜查了那栋房子，寻找被偷的珠宝。</p><footer>译林① – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As they entered the forest, they began to search for a suitable camping spot.
当他们进入森林时，就开始寻找合适的露营地点。</p><footer>2009 江西改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I searched the Internet for the train schedule and some hotel information.
我在网上搜索火车时刻表和一些旅馆信息。</p><footer>2010 北京书面表达改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(对某人) 搜身</strong></h4>
<p>(especially of the police) to carefully examine sth / sb for sth that is hidden：</p>
<ul>
<li>search sb (for sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police searched her for drugs. 
警察搜查她,看她身上是否藏有毒品。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>探索；思索</strong></h4>
<p>to try to find an answer to a problem：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She paused, <strong>searching for</strong> inspiration. 
她停了下来寻找灵感。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The general manager promised to <strong>search into</strong> the matter. 
总经理答应深入调查此事。</p></div></div>